## ROUTE RELATION FLOW

Authentication: /login → LoginPage → authService.login() → POST /api/auth/login → auth.login() → User.findOne() → MongoDB → JWT tokens → Zustand store

CRUD: /:module → CrudPage → modulesConfig[module] → useQuery() → GET /api/:module → controller.getAll() → Model.find() → paginated data → display table → Create/Edit modal → useMutation() → POST/PUT → validation → database → AuditLog → invalidate cache

Protected Route: any protected route → ProtectedRoute → check Zustand token → if no token redirect /login → if token exists → GET /api/auth/profile → verify JWT → render component

Dashboard: /dashboard → DashboardPage (lazy loaded) → useQuery() for stats → /api/dashboard/summary, /api/users/count → aggregation pipelines → display charts/cards

Search/Filter: search input → useDebounce() → trigger useQuery() refetch → GET /api/:module?search=term&page=1 → regex search on indexed fields → filtered results

